## When embedding the chat UI

The library provides five composable UI components. The main entry point is `Component_ChatPanel`:

```tsx
import {Component_ChatPanel} from '@nu-art/ts-messaging-frontend';

// Drop in anywhere — renders full chat with message list, input, and thread panel:
<Component_ChatPanel topicId={topicId} />
```

### Component hierarchy

| Component | Purpose | Props |
|-----------|---------|-------|
| `Component_ChatPanel` | Main embeddable chat container | `topicId` |
| `Component_MessageList` | Scrollable message list with load-more | `messages`, `hasMore`, `onLoadMore`, `onReplyClick` |
| `Component_MessageInput` | Text input + send button | `onSend` |
| `Component_MessageBubble` | Single message renderer | `message`, `onReplyClick` |
| `Component_ThreadPanel` | Thread view for replies | `parentMessage`, `onClose` |

### Building a custom layout

Use the individual components to compose a custom chat layout:

```tsx
import {Component_MessageList} from '@nu-art/ts-messaging-frontend';
import {Component_MessageInput} from '@nu-art/ts-messaging-frontend';

// In your custom component:
<div className="my-chat">
	<Component_MessageList
		messages={messages}
		hasMore={hasMore}
		onLoadMore={loadMore}
		onReplyClick={handleReply}
	/>
	<Component_MessageInput onSend={handleSend} />
</div>
```

### Theming

All CSS classes are BEM-namespaced under `ts-messaging__*`. Override at the app level:

```scss
.ts-messaging__chat-panel { /* main container */ }
.ts-messaging__chat-panel__main { /* message list + input area */ }
.ts-messaging__chat-panel__thread { /* thread sidebar */ }
.ts-messaging__bubble { /* single message */ }
.ts-messaging__input { /* input area */ }
.ts-messaging__message-list { /* scrollable list */ }
.ts-messaging__thread-panel { /* thread container */ }
```

